You might’ve seen the thread where I did this before, but that approach last time had a few problems, which I’ll get to later.

I created a combination of like 10 different programs (this was a pain to make) that pulls from the github code search website (the api is using an outdated version of code search that doesn’t have all frc teams) to create a list of every public code repo with ProjectYear: 2025 in .wpilibpreferences. (This won’t include teams running 2025Beta like 449 (added a section for that), or python teams like 4774, who don’t have that in wpilibprefs, I can fix this if theres interest).

The result is this spreadsheet with 2713 3310 codebases across 1491 teams, sorted by season epa.
I think this is can be a really really helpful resource for people learning to code or in general when searching for a team’s codebase. I’ve left the “Includes Main Robot Code” column open to editing so that, like in the previous one, we can categorize each team’s codebases.

If anyone has suggestions for what changes I should make to the sheet or what community contributions we might want to go for (like categorizing what vision system they use, drivetrain, etc) please share.
If you want edit access lmk.

I’m running the second script right now, so I’ll publish those repos sometime in the next half hour or so.

It’s really unfortunate that there’s no deterministic way to search github code or solve this problem another way. But hopefully as it stands this is still a good enough resource for teams. Thanks for the help everyone!
